d Conic Sections | year=2009 | author1=David Dennis | author2=Susan Addington | website=Mathematical Intentions | publisher=quadrivium.info | url=http://quadrivium.info/MathInt/Notes/Apollonius.pdf}}\n* {{cite web | title=Can You Really Derive Conic Formulae from a Cone? | first=Gary S. | last=Stoudt | publisher=Mathematical Association of America | accessdate=March 28, 2017 | url=http://www.maa.org/press/periodicals/convergence/can-you-really-derive-conic-formulae-from-a-cone}}\n* {{cite thesis | type=Ph.D. |last=McKinney | first=Colin Bryan Powell | date=2010 | title=Conjugate diameters: Apollonius of Perga and Eutocius of Ascalon | publisher=University of Iowa | url=http://ir.uiowa.edu/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?article=1896&context=etd}}\n{{Greek astronomy}}\n{{Greek mathematics}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Apollonius of Perga}}\n[[Category:Ancient Greek astronomers]]\n[[Category:Ancient Greek mathematicians]]\n[[Category:Ancient Greek inventors]]\n[[Category:Pamphylians]]\n[[Category:History of geometry]]\n[[Category:260s BC births]]\n[[Category:190s BC deaths]]\n", "name_user": "188.146.96.117", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(Adding his latin name)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Apollonius_of_Perga"}
{"title_page": "Information Services Group (ISG)", "text_new": "{{Infobox company\n| name                = Information Services Group\n| logo                = \n| type                = [[Public Company]]\n| traded_as           = {{NASDAQ was|[http://www.nasdaq.com/symbol/iii III]}}\n| industry            = Technology Advisory Services, Technology Research\n| founded             = \n| key_people          = \n| services            = \n| revenue             = {{nowrap|{{increase}} [[US$]] 276 million <small>(2018)</small>}}\n| operating_income    = {{nowrap|{{increase}} [[US$]] 13 million <small>(2018)</small>}}\n| num_employees       = {{nowrap|1,300 <small>(2018)</small>}}\n| website             = https://www.ISG-one.com\n| footnotes           = <ref name=\"10-K 2016\">{{cite web|url=https://www.stamfordadvocate.com/business/article/ISG-signs-lease-for-new-Stamford-HQ-12302738.php|title=ISG signs lease for new Stamford HQ|publisher=[[Stamford Advocate]]|accessdate=April 12, 2019}}</ref>\n| headquarters        = \n}}\n\n'''Information Services Group (ISG)''', is a technology research and advisory firm. The firm was founded in 2006.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/companies/information-services-group/|title=Information Services Group|website=Forbes|language=en|access-date=2020-01-22}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.stamfordadvocate.com/local/article/Stamford-based-Information-Services-Group-10687947.php|title=Stamford-based Information Services Group acquires Texas firm|last=Schott|first=Paul|date=2016-12-02|website=StamfordAdvocate|access-date=2020-01-22}}</ref>\n\n== History ==\nISG was founded in [[Stamford, Connecticut]] by current chairman and CEO Michael P. Connors<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/alisoncoleman/2018/03/01/why-a-high-profile-corporate-career-was-the-making-of-this-global-entrepreneur/#5478b745b889|title=Why A High Profile Corporate Career Was The Making Of This Global Entrepreneur|website=Forbes|accessdate=12 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/companies/information-services-group/|title=Information Services Group|website=Forbes|language=en|access-date=2020-01-24}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.reuters.comundefined/|title=III.OQ - Information Services Group, Inc. Profile {{!}} Reuters|last=Editorial|first=Reuters|website=www.reuters.comundefined|language=en|access-date=2020-01-23}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://markets.businessinsider.com/stocks/iii/company-profile|title=Information Services Group Company Profile {{!}} Markets Insider|last=|first=|date=|website=Business Insider|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-01-23}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/III/company-people|title=III {{!}} Information Services Group Inc. Company Profile & Executives - WSJ|website=www.wsj.com|access-date=2020-01-23}}</ref> Prior to becoming CEO of ISG, Connors was chairman and CEO of [[Nielsen ratings|Nielsen Media and Measurement]], and had leadership roles at [[American Express]] and [[Sprint Corporation|Sprint]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://chiefexecutive.net/isg-ceo-values-entrepreneurial-spirit-drove-growth/|title=ISG CEO: Values, Entrepreneurial Spirit Drove Company\u2019s Growth|last=Perna|first=Gabriel|date=2018-09-13|website=ChiefExecutive.net|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref>\n\nIn November 2007, ISG acquired TPI, a private advisory services firm that helps guide enterprises through BPO engagements.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hrotoday.com/news/sourcing/information-services-group-acquires-tpi-for-280m/|title=Information Services Group Acquires TPI for $280M|last=HROToday|date=2007-05-04|website=HRO Today|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-23}}</ref> In 2011, ISG acquired analytics and public sector technology advisory services Compass and STA Consulting, respectively.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.stamfordadvocate.com/business/article/ISG-buys-public-sector-firm-for-9-million-1019055.php|title=ISG buys public sector firm for $9 million|website=Stamford Advocate|accessdate=12 April 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn 2014, ISG also acquired client satisfaction benchmarking and research firm CCI Consulting Pty Ltd (CCI).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.computerwoche.de/a/experton-verabschiedet-sich-unter-das-dach-der-isg,3224881|title=Experton says goodbye to ISG|website=Computerwoche|accessdate=12 April 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn 2016, ISG added vendor benchmarking services with the acquisition of Experton Group AG.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mrweb.com/drno/news22356.htm|title=ISG Buys German Firm Experton|website=Mrweb|accessdate=12 April 2019}}</ref>\n\nAt the end of 2016, ISG acquired Alsbridge, a U.S.-based sourcing, automation and digital transformation advisory firm.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.stamfordadvocate.com/local/article/Stamford-based-Information-Services-Group-10687947.php|title=Stamford-based Information Services Group acquires Texas firm|website=Stamford Advocate|accessdate=12 April 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn October 2018, the firm released ISG Blockchain Now to help companies use blockchain technology.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://westfaironline.com/107710/information-services-group-introduces-blockchain-product/|title=Information Services Group introduces blockchain product|last=Hall|first=Phil|date=2018-10-10|website=Westfair Communications|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-22}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n<!-- Inline citations added to your article will automatically display here. See en.wikipedia.org/wiki/WP:REFB for instructions on how to add citations. -->\n{{reflist}}\n\n\n{{Company-stub}}\n{{Uncategorized stub|date=April 2020}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox company\n| name                = Information Services Group\n| logo                = \n| type                = [[Public Company]]\n| traded_as           = {{NASDAQ was|[http://www.nasdaq.com/symbol/iii III]}}\n| industry            = Technology Advisory Services, Technology Research\n| founded      